Author : Sunopsis Updates by: support-de@sunopsis.com Version : 4.1 Last Update : AUG-2006
Description: - Loading Knowledge Module - Loads data from any ISO-92 compliant database to a Sybase ASE Server database using bcp utility. - This module uses Sunopsis Command SnpsSqlUnload to extract data in a temporary file. Data is loaded in the target temporary Sybase ASE table created dynamically using the bcp utility. - When using this module on a journalized source table, the Journaling table is first updated to flag the records consumed and then cleaned from these records at the end of the interface.
Changes: - Added options for FIELD_SEP, BCP_BATCH_SIZE, FETCH_SIZE (unload) - BCP is started via a Jython system call
Restrictions: - Target work database must be set to 'select into/bulk copy' option. - The option DEFAULT_DIRECTORY indicates the location of the temporary generated file. It must be accessible by both Sunopsis Agent and the Sybase ASE Instance. - Sunopsis Agent must have bcp installed. - The option BCP_DIRECTORY indicates the location of the bcp program. It should not contain whitespaces. - For performance reasons, it is recommanded to install Sunopsis agent either on the source or on the target server.
Temp. Directory for the data file

Directory where the temporary data file is created. This directory must be a valid path on the machine running the Sunopsis Agent. Examples: - On Windows: D:\MyDatafiles\MyTemporaryFolder - On Unix / Linux: /usr/tmp
Directory where the BCP program is installed on the agent's machine.
Set this option to NO if you wish to retain temporary objects (tables, files and scripts) after integration. Useful for debugging.

<? /* For every datatype in this string, Sunopsis will generate a NOT NULL column in the work table. For all other datatypes, NULL cols will be created in the C$ table. This string is being analyzed by evaluating for every column the following statement:
notNullDataTypes.indexOf("[DEST_WRI_DT]") >= 0
If this expression evaluates to true, the string "NOT" is being added before the "NULL" keyword. */
String notNullDataTypes = "BIT"; ?>

<% if ("C".equals(snpRef.getJrnInfo( "JRN_METHOD"))) { %> /* Consistant journalization detected. */ /* Lock should be done by a specific step in a package */ <% } else { %> update <%=snpRef.getTable( "L" , "JRN_NAME" , "A" )%> set JRN_CONSUMED = '1' where (1=1) <%=snpRef.getJrnFilter()%> <% } %>

import os
loadcmd =r"<%=snpRef.getUserExit("BCP_DIRECTORY")%>/bcp <%=snpRef.getTable("L", "COLL_NAME", "W")%> in <%=snpRef.getUserExit("DEFAULT_DIRECTORY")%>/<%=snpRef.getInfo("COLL_NAME")%>.bcp -c -t'<%=snpRef.getOption("FIELD_SEPARATOR")%>' -b<%=snpRef.getOption("BCP_BATCH_SIZE")%> -S<%=snpRef.getInfo("DEST_DSERV_NAME")%> -U<%=snpRef.getInfo("DEST_USER_NAME")%> -P<%=snpRef.getInfo("DEST_PASS")%> -J<%=snpRef.getOption("BCP_CHARSET_ENCODING")%> > <%=snpRef.getUserExit("DEFAULT_DIRECTORY")%>/<%=snpRef.getInfo("COLL_NAME")%>.in.log"
print loadcmd
if os.system(loadcmd) <> 0: raise "BCPl failed:", "See <%=snpRef.getUserExit("DEFAULT_DIRECTORY")%>/<%=snpRef.getInfo("COLL_NAME")%>.in.log or agent output for details"

<% if ("C".equals(snpRef.getJrnInfo( "JRN_METHOD"))) { %> /* Consistant journalization detected. */ /* Lock should be done by a specific step in a package */ <% } else { %> delete from <%=snpRef.getTable( "L" , "JRN_NAME" , "A" )%> where JRN_CONSUMED = '1' <%=snpRef.getJrnFilter()%> <% } %>
